As of 2009, Toyota officially lists approximately 70 different models sold under its namesake brand, including sedans, coupes, vans, trucks, hybrids, and crossovers.<ref name="Toyotaworld">{{Cite web |title=Toyota Product Line up 2009 |url=http://www.toyota.co.jp/en/about_toyota/in_the_world/pdf2009/line_up_en.pdf |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722100311/http://www.toyota.co.jp/en/about_toyota/in_the_world/pdf2009/line_up_en.pdf |archive-date=July 22, 2011 |access-date=September 11, 2010}}</ref>{{primary source inline|date=December 2023}} Many of these models are produced as passenger sedans, which range from the subcompact [[Toyota Yaris]], compact [[Toyota Corolla|Corolla]], to mid-size [[Toyota Camry|Camry]] and full-size [[Toyota Avalon|Avalon]].<ref name="Toyotaworld" />{{primary source inline|date=December 2023}} Minivans include the [[Toyota Innova|Innova]], [[Toyota Alphard|Alphard/Vellfire]], [[Toyota Sienna|Sienna]], and others.<ref name="Toyotaworld" />{{primary source inline|date=December 2023}} Several small cars, such as the [[Scion xB|xB]] and [[Scion tC|tC]], were sold under the [[Scion (automobile)|Scion]] brand.<ref name="Toyotaworld" />{{primary source inline|date=December 2023}}{{clear}}

