Toyota SUV and crossover line-up grew quickly in the late 2010s to 2020s due to the market shift to SUVs. Toyota crossovers range from the subcompact [[Toyota Yaris Cross|Yaris Cross]] and [[Toyota C-HR|C-HR]], compact [[Corolla Cross]] and [[Toyota RAV4|RAV4]], to midsize [[Toyota Venza|Harrier/Venza]] and [[Toyota Kluger|Kluger/Highlander]].<ref name="Toyotaworld" />{{primary source inline|date=December 2023}} Other crossovers include the [[Toyota Raize|Raize]], [[Toyota Urban Cruiser|Urban Cruiser]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=June 13, 2021 |title=New Toyota Land Cruiser is 200 kg lighter, more advanced than its predecessor |language=en |work=CarWale |url=https://www.carwale.com/news/new-toyota-land-cruiser-is-200-kg-lighter-more-advanced-than-its-predecessor/}}</ref> Toyota SUVs range from the midsize [[Toyota Fortuner|Fortuner]] to full-size [[Toyota Land Cruiser|Land Cruiser]].<ref name="Toyotaworld" />{{primary source inline|date=December 2023}} Other SUVs include the [[Toyota Rush|Rush]], [[Toyota Land Cruiser Prado|Prado]], [[Toyota FJ Cruiser|FJ Cruiser]], [[Toyota 4Runner|4Runner]], and [[Toyota Sequoia|Sequoia]].<ref name="Toyotaworld" />{{primary source inline|date=December 2023}}
